Here's what you need:

## XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <ContentView>
                <Label Text="No items found."
                       HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
            </ContentView>
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

## ViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    // Pull-to-refresh: reload from API, then set IsRefreshing = false
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        });
        IsRefreshing = false;
    }

    // Selection: navigate to detail, then clear selection
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", new Dictionary<string, object>
        {
            { "Item", CurrentItem }
        });
        CurrentItem = null; // reset so re-selecting the same item works
    }
}
```

## Key bindings explained

| XAML property | ViewModel property | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item> Items` | Data source — must be `ObservableCollection` so add/remove updates the UI |
| `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | `Item? CurrentItem` | Tracks selected item; set to `null` after navigation to allow re-selection |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on tap → triggers navigation |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Fires on pull-to-refresh → reloads data |
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` (TwoWay) | `bool IsRefreshing` | Controls the spinner; **you must set it to `false`** when done |

**Important rules:**
- Always update the collection on the **UI thread** (`MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`).
- Never use `ViewCell` — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, or any `View` as the template root.
- Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- Wrap custom `EmptyView` content in a `ContentView`.
